    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Fluid Pan, Gasket and Filter Installation</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Prior to installing the transmission filter, make sure that the old fluid filter seal has been
                    removed.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new fluid filter and seal assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0701035" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0055963.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Tighten all the transmission fluid pan bolts in a crisscross pattern.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the fluid pan gasket and fluid pan.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Tighten to 15 Nm (11 lb-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0701036" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0055943.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the transmission fluid drain plug.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Tighten to 25 Nm (18 lb-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0701037" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0055937.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>The use of any other transmission fluid than specified can result in the transmission failing to
                    operate in a normal manner or transmission failure.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill the transmission.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Add 7.0 liters (7.5 qts) of clean automatic transmission fluid to the transmission through the
                fluid filler tube.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Start the engine. Move the transmission range selector lever through all the gear ranges,
                checking for engagements.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the vehicle in NEUTRAL, engine running and the transmission at normal operating
                temperature 66-77&#176;C (150-170&#176;F), check and adjust the transmission fluid level and check for
                any leaks. If fluid is needed, add fluid in increments of 0.24 liter (0.5 pint) until the correct level
                is achieved (fluid should be in the cross-hatched area of the fluid level indicator).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
